                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d672">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.51/1733: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-02-29T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 29, 1940—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>45. Your 74, February 28, 9 p.m. Francis White states that the Council has
                    refrained from all comment of any type whatsoever, formal or informal, as
                    regards the possibility of a debt settlement with Brazil.</p>
                <p>Please correct Bouças’ impression and, if necessary, any impression that Aranha
                    may have to the contrary.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
